{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LzxN5vvC8UFeL2tZzCdkvU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Let me create a comprehensive summary report:\n\n## Analysis Report: `entries` Column Mismatch\n\n### Root Cause\nThe tests are failing with **\"column 'entries' of relation 'rounds' does not exist\"** because:\n\n1. **The `db.ts` code (line 309)** is trying to INSERT into an `entries` column:\n   ```sql\n   INSERT INTO rounds (pda, game, creator, server_key, secret, commitment, amount_lamports, side, match_id, phase, entries)\n   ```\n\n2. **Migration 007 adds this column**, but the **test database has not run the migration**. The schema only has migrations 001-006 applied, which means the `entries` column doesn't exist.\n\n3. **The tests don't run migrations automatically**. They just:\n   - Connect to PostgreSQL\n   - Call `TRUNCATE rounds, operator_events RESTART IDENTITY`\n   - Run tests directly\n\n### Evidence\n\n**File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts` (lines 73, 89, 169-173, 286-301, 309-321)**\n- The `Round` interface has `entries: unknown | null` (line 73)\n- The `InsertRoundParams` interface has optional `entries` parameter (line 89)\n- There's a `updateRoundEntries()` method (lines 170-173)\n- The `normalizeRound()` function handles entries parsing (lines 294-299)\n- The INSERT statement includes `entries` column (line 309)\n\n**File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/007_round_entries.sql`**\n```sql\nALTER TABLE rounds ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS entries JSONB DEFAULT NULL;\n```\nThis migration adds the column but the tests don't apply it.\n\n**Files: `endpoints.test.ts` and `integration.test.ts`**\n- Both tests only run `TRUNCATE` in `beforeEach`\n- Neither calls `runMigrations()` or applies the migration schema\n- They assume the database schema already has the `entries` column\n\n### Why This Is a Problem\n\nThe code in `create.ts` (lines 173-185) calls `db.insertRound()` which tries to INSERT with the `entries` column. Since the test database schema doesn't have migration 007 applied, the INSERT fails.\n\n### Solution\n\nThe test database needs migration 007 applied **before the tests run**. This should happen either:\n1. As part of the test setup (run all pending migrations before each test suite), OR\n2. As a prerequisite setup step that the devcontainer/CI ensures has run\n\n**Currently:** No migrations are run in the test setup, so any new column additions in recent migrations will cause test failures until the database is manually migrated.\n\n---\n\n### Files Involved\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts` | DB client with INSERT statement that references `entries` |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts` | Calls `db.insertRound()` |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/007_round_entries.sql` | Migration that adds the `entries` column |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` | Test that truncates but doesn't migrate |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` | Test that truncates but doesn't migrate |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad9165d5fdcdd49af (use SendMessage with to: 'ad9165d5fdcdd49af' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59729\ntool_uses: 16\nduration_ms: 189723</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9dfcb3ed-4930-49c9-8526-cce92c2e50e0","uuid":"7c351888-98eb-43e7-8928-c1e7afdd5b67","timestamp":"2026-03-19T20:22:35.445Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand why backend tests are failing with `column \"entries\" of relation \"rounds\" does not exist`. Check these things:\n\n1. Read `services/backend/src/__tests__/endpoint