n- The INSERT statement includes `entries` column (line 309)\n\n**File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/007_round_entries.sql`**\n```sql\nALTER TABLE rounds ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS entries JSONB DEFAULT NULL;\n```\nThis migration adds the column but the tests don't apply it.\n\n**Files: `endpoints.test.ts` and `integration.test.ts`**\n- Both tests only run `TRUNCATE` in `beforeEach`\n- Neither calls `runMigrations()` or applies the migration schema\n- They assume the database schema already has the `entries` column\n\n### Why This Is a Problem\n\nThe code in `create.ts` (lines 173-185) calls `db.insertRound()` which tries to INSERT with the `entries` column. Since the test database schema doesn't have migration 007 applied, the INSERT fails.\n\n### Solution\n\nThe test database needs migration 007 applied **before the tests run**. This should happen either:\n1. As part of the test setup (run all pending migrations before each test suite), OR\n2. As a prerequisite setup step that the devcontainer/CI ensures has run\n\n**Currently:** No migrations are run in the test setup, so any new column additions in recent migrations will cause test failures until the database is manually migrated.\n\n---\n\n### Files Involved\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts` | DB client with INSERT statement that references `entries` |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts` | Calls `db.insertRound()` |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/007_round_entries.sql` | Migration that adds the `entries` column |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` | Test that truncates but doesn't migrate |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` | Test that truncates but doesn't migrate |"}],"totalDuration